word examines the scholarly and pedagogical setting within which Strayer produced his book, and how this both enhanced its accessibility and informed its focus on peculiarly English and French accomplishments in early state formation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aEurope -- Politics and government. 0aMiddle Ages. 0aMiddle Ages.;State, The -- History -- To 1500.;Europe -- Politics and government. 0aState, The -- History -- To 1500. 0aState, ThexHistoryyTo 1500. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh1 aJordan, William Chester.1 aTilly, Charles.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044250240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140082857940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400828579423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400828579.jpg  a978-3-11-044250-2  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK